Package edu.umaryland.igs.idea

Interface Summary
CustomRenderable The CustomRenderable interface is implemented by classes whose objects can be converted to an AWT or Swing component designed to take up part of a table cell.
 

Class Summary
AffixLengthLimiter AffixLengthLimiter is an extension of StateDependentInputVerifier for text fields which are converted to filename affixes (prefixes, suffixes or infixes), such as omega.
BackwardCompatibilityManager BackwardCompatibilityManager contains static methods useful for reading configurations saved using old versions of IDEA and initializing them to be compliant with the current code.
BlankParameter BlankParameter represents a parameter with no value.
BooleanParameter BooleanParameter represents an IDEA parameter which allows the user to choose one of two options (not necessarily true and false).
BrowserLauncher BrowserLauncher contains code that launches the user's default web browser.
DatasetListVerifier Class DatasetListVerifier is a FileFormatVerifier for the dataset list used in multi-dataset mode.
DatasetVerifier A dataset list's constituent sequence and tree filenames are validated by instances of anonymous subclasses of class DatasetVerifier, which extends OmegaBasedFilenameLengthLimiter.
FaultTolerantFontConverter FaultTolerantFontConverter is designed to help XStream read fonts from a saved configuration.
FileAvailabilityVerifier FileAvailabilityVerifier, the degenerate FileFormatVerifier, simply requires that a file exist and be non-empty and readable.
FileFormatVerifier FileFormatVerifier is an extension of FileVerifier common to text fields which expect the name of a file that must have a particular format.
FilenameLengthLimiter FilenameLengthLimiter is an extension of FileVerifier common to text fields which restrict user input based on a maximum filename length imposed by PAML.
FileParameter FileParameter represents a user-specifiable filename parameter which determines IDEA behavior.
FileVerifier FileVerifier is an abstract extension of StateDependentInputVerifier common to filename text fields.
HistogramDemo HistogramDemo gives a demonstration of class Histogram.
HistogramDialog HistogramDialog displays a dialog which allows the user to choose a model upon which a histogram will be based when the user clicks "Display".
HistogramWindow HistogramWindow displays a Histogram in a titled window with a save button, radio buttons for changing the selected model and a slider for changing the number of bins.
HorizontalOffsetMetalSliderUI HorizontalOffsetMetalSliderUI is a custom UI for the "Number of bins" slider that paints major tick marks at the locations of its custom labels.
IDEAColors IDEAColors contains color constants and color-related code that may be used throughout IDEA.
IDEAConfiguration IDEAConfiguration encapsulates all the configuration for a particular run of IDEA, including the parameter sets.
IDEAConstants IDEAConstants contains non-color constants used throughout IDEA.
IDEAInputGUI IDEAInputGUI is the main class in the IDEA suite, which is designed to allow users to perform analyses of molecular evolution and view their results.
IDEAOutputGUI IDEAOutputGUI is the main class for the output portion of the IDEA suite, which is allow users to view results of completed analyses.
IncompatibilityDemonstration  
LikelihoodData The class LikelihoodData encapsulates the results of a likelihood ratio test and the data used to arrive at those results.
LocalRadioButton The radio button members of a MultipleChoiceParameter are instances of type LocalRadioButton, which extends JRadioButton to allow more leniency in deserialization.
MouseOverListener The class MouseOverListener serves to replace the function of the tool tip because tool tips on rendered components are inactive.
MultipleChoiceParameter MultipleChoiceParameter represents an IDEA parameter that allows the user to choose one of multiple options.
OmegaBasedFilenameLengthLimiter OmegaBasedFilenameLengthLimiter is an extension of FilenameLengthLimiter common to length-limited filename fields whose contents will be converted to filenames parameterized by user-specified omega values.
PairwiseSummaryTableModel PairwiseSummaryTableModel is the subclass of SummaryTableModel used for tables derived from pairwise IDEA analyses (those for which all datasets have exactly two sequences).
PAMLParameterSet PAMLParameterSet represents a grouping of PAML parameters.
Parameter Parameter represents a user-specifiable parameter which determines IDEA behavior.
ParameterExplanation ParameterExplanation represents an explanation for users about the interpretation of a parameter.
ParameterSet ParameterSet represents a grouping of parameters.
SiteSubstitutionModel The SiteSubstitutionModel class represents one of codeml's site models.
StandardFileParameter StandardFileParameter represents a filename parameter which allows the user to choose among default choices or enter a new one.
StandardSummaryTableModel StandardSummaryTableModel is the subclass of SummaryTableModel used for tables derived from non-pairwise IDEA analyses (those with at least one dataset having three or more sequences).
StateDependentInputVerifier StateDependentInputVerifier is an extension of TextFieldInputVerifier common to text fields whose validation depends on the current values of other parameters or perhaps on other aspects of IDEA's current state.
SummaryTableButton SummaryTableButton represents a button in a summary table's header.
SummaryTableCellRenderer SummaryTableCellRenderer is the custom renderer for all rows except the header row.
SummaryTableHeaderRenderer SummaryTableHeaderRenderer is the custom renderer for the header row.
SummaryTableModel SummaryTableModel represents the back end for the table displayed by IDEAOutputGUI.
TextFieldInputVerifier TextFieldInputVerifier is a convenience extension of InputVerifier that passes calls to verify through to its own verifyText method, which subclasses define.
 

Enum Summary
IDEAInputGUI.Status IDEA's status can take one of four values: NOT_STARTED, RUNNING, SUCCEEDED or FAILED.
